	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Finally got this Unholy Symbol of Bertoxxulous for my level six human priest of Bertoxxulous. The quest itself is very hard to do, and impossible without a druid and maybe even a ranger. Needed the ranger to track down the NPC that you need to get the Sprig of Wormwood from; she was'nt North and West of the mill, more like North and East, near the minotaur guards. You also need a druid or an enchanter to charm the female rat so you can give her the vial of infectious fluids or whatever it's called that Evah Xokez gives you back at the Dark Reflection. As for the Brittle Skeletons, they are at least yellow to my level six twink and hit hard, and drop the Diseased Bone Marrow maybe one in eight times; must've killed at least twenty brittle skeletons yesterday before I got both of them. <br><br>But despite how hard the quest is, the reward when you're in a group and cast your Disease Cloud spell on a mob and your party gets the message that your Symbol of Bertoxxulous Symbol begins to glow is all the reward I need. Thanks Verant, and don't forget to give us Priests of Bertoxxulous a Disciple and Warden symbol further down the road.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
